er matrix\nspectrum. This is explicitly implemented for the integrable quantum models\nassociated to the higher spin representations of the general quasi-periodic\nY(gl2) Yang-Baxter algebra. Our SoV approach also leads to the construction of\na Q-operator in terms of the fused transfer matrices. Finally, we show that the\nQ-operator family can be equivalently used as the family of commuting conserved\ncharges enabling to construct our SoV bases.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 15 Mar 2019 16:02:45 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 4 Jan 2021 16:19:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-02-10"}
