e distribution of Chinese asterisms, and show that its large\nextension was inconsistent with the lunar halo hypothesis. Conversely, the\nstreaks of white vapour penetrating the eight Chinese asterisms can be\nreproduced if we consider auroral-ray structures at altitudes between 97 km and\n170 km, along geomagnetic field lines between the L-shells L=1.55 and 1.64. Our\ninvestigations show that we should consider candidate auroral records in\nhistorical documents not on the basis of the newly suggested a priori criteria\nby NN15 but on all the available observational evidence.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 15 Mar 2019 21:11:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-05-01"}
